content:
To keep stakeholders informed without sending a new broadcast Slack message, update a broadcast Slack message's incident fields to reflect the latest changes.

Customer Service Incident Management must be enabled. Broadcast Slack messages must be enabled. Broadcast topics must be assigned to Slack channels.

You can update only broadcast Slack messages that weren't deleted or that didn't previously fail to send, update, or delete.

Go to the incident related lists and find the Broadcast Communications related list.
Find the broadcast Slack message you want to update. From the broadcast communication's dropdown, select Update Broadcast Slack Message.
Review the updated message, click Next, and then Done.
title: Updating Broadcast Slack Messages in Service Cloud
